TITLE: Error Handling for Notifee Notifications in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to implement error handling when displaying notifications using Notifee. This pattern wraps the notification creation in a try/catch block to capture any validation errors that may occur during notification setup.
SOURCE: https://github.com/invertase/notifee/blob/main/docs/react-native/debugging.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
try {
  await notifee.displayNotification({
    title: 'Chat with Joe Bloggs',
    body: 'A new message has been received from a user.',
    ...
  });
} catch (e) {
  console.log(e);
}
```

