TITLE: Creating and Saving FCM Device Tokens in React Native
DESCRIPTION: Retrieves the device-specific FCM token and saves it to a backend API. This code should be run on app bootstrap to ensure the token is current, as tokens can change. It requires the @react-native-firebase/messaging package.
SOURCE: https://github.com/invertase/notifee/blob/main/docs/react-native/integrations/fcm.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import messaging from '@react-native-firebase/messaging';

async function onAppBootstrap() {
  // Register the device with FCM
  await messaging().registerDeviceForRemoteMessages();

  // Get the token
  const token = await messaging().getToken();

  // Save the token
  await postToApi('/users/1234/tokens', { token });
}
```

