TITLE: Handling Channel Events with Notifee
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to listen for and handle various channel-related events such as app blocking, channel blocking, and channel group blocking.
SOURCE: https://github.com/invertase/notifee/blob/main/docs/react-native/android/channels.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import notifee, { EventType } from '@notifee/react-native';

notifee.onForegroundEvent(({ type, detail }) => {
  if (type === EventType.APP_BLOCKED) {
    console.log('User toggled app blocked', detail.blocked);
  }

  if (type === EventType.CHANNEL_BLOCKED) {
    console.log('User toggled channel block', detail.channel.id, detail.blocked);
  }

  if (type === EventType.CHANNEL_GROUP_BLOCKED) {
    console.log('User toggled channel group block', detail.channelGroup.id, detail.blocked);
  }
});
```

