TITLE: Updating a Foreground Service Notification with Progress in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Updates an existing foreground service notification to show progress. This snippet demonstrates how to maintain the same notification ID while updating its content, such as a progress indicator.
SOURCE: https://github.com/invertase/notifee/blob/main/docs/react-native/android/foreground-service.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
notifee.registerForegroundService((notification) => {
  return new Promise(() => {
    // Example task subscriber
    onTaskUpdate(async (task) => {
      if (task.update) {
        notifee.displayNotification({
          id: notification.id,
          body: notification.body,
          android: {
            ...notification.android,
            progress: {
              max: task.update.total,
              current: task.update.current,
            },
          },
        });
      }

      if (task.complete) {
        await notifee.stopForegroundService()
      }
    });
  });
});
```

