TITLE: Managing Power Manager Settings for Android Notifications
DESCRIPTION: This code retrieves information about the device's power manager and guides users to adjust their settings to prevent the app from being killed. It checks if the device has specific power management settings and provides navigation to those settings.
SOURCE: https://github.com/invertase/notifee/blob/main/docs/react-native/android/background-restrictions.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// 1. get info on the device and the Power Manager settings
const powerManagerInfo = await notifee.getPowerManagerInfo();
if (powerManagerInfo.activity) {
  // 2. ask your users to adjust their settings
  Alert.alert(
      'Restrictions Detected',
      'To ensure notifications are delivered, please adjust your settings to prevent the app from being killed',
      [
        // 3. launch intent to navigate the user to the appropriate screen
        {
          text: 'OK, open settings',
          onPress: async () => await notifee.openPowerManagerSettings(),
        },
        {
          text: "Cancel",
          onPress: () => console.log("Cancel Pressed"),
          style: "cancel"
        },
      ],
      { cancelable: false }
    );
};
```

